{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Add ESA for pregnancy to the qualifying criteria for maternity allowance.",
        "additional_details": "Lack of employment means they no longer qualify for the maternity allowance scheme where they previously would have. Leaving them without ANY maternity leave or pay. I therefore ask the government to include \u2018ESA for pregnancy reasons\u2019 in the qualifying criteria for the maternity allowance scheme for as long as the Government advises pregnant women to socially distance themselves.",
        "background": "On March 16th 2020 pregnant women were listed as \u2018vulnerable\u2019 and asked to remain home for 12 weeks by government. Pregnant women who have lost jobs have been unable to secure new ones or those in job transition stages have seen job offers \u2018put on hold\u2019 are therefore not working or seen as employed.",
